# Generated Talos machine configs contain PKI material (CA private key,
# bootstrap token, encryption secrets) — never commit them as-is.
# See controlplane.patch.yaml for the non-secret machine config we DO commit.
#
# TODO: replace this gitignore-based approach with SOPS-encrypted committed
# configs, or a Secrets Manager round-trip per
# vault/decisions/secrets-manager-for-tf-providers.md
controlplane.yaml
worker.yaml
controlplane.patched.yaml
worker.patched.yaml
talosconfig
secrets.yaml

# Local backup patterns (zip archives, "copy of" folders, .bak files).
# Dana keeps off-laptop backups of the secret-bearing files until the
# proper SOPS/Secrets-Manager stash lands.
*.zip
*.bak
* copy/
* copy
